Package net.groboclown.retval.monitor

Interface NotCompletedListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoggingNotCompletedListener
    public interface NotCompletedListener
    A pluggable way to change out listening for notifications when a monitor detects that an object was not completed.

      void instanceNotCompleted​(java.lang.String monitorName, java.lang.String instanceName, java.lang.StackTraceElement[] creationPoint)

    • Method Detail

      • instanceNotCompleted

        void instanceNotCompleted​(@Nonnull
                          java.lang.String monitorName,
                          @Nonnull
                          java.lang.String instanceName,
                          @Nonnull
                          java.lang.StackTraceElement[] creationPoint)
        Called when a monitor detects that a registered instance went out of scope from the JVM but was never marked as completed.

        The stack trace records the moment when the instance was last registered with the monitor. In cases where the monitor check is passed to multiple objects, this should reflect the most recent stack.

        Parameters:
        monitorName - name of the monitor, usually indicating the type of instances stored.
        instanceName - the toString for this registered instance (it can't be the instance itself due to memory references at GC time).
        creationPoint - stack trace for when the instance was registered.
